{"sections":[],"relationshipsSections":[{"kind":"relationships","type":"conformsTo","title":"Conforms To","identifiers":["doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/ShapeStyle","doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/s8CopyableP","doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/s8SendableP"]}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"patch":0,"minor":3},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI"]]},"topicSections":[{"anchor":"Default-Implementations","title":"Default Implementations","identifiers":["doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Material\/ShapeStyle-Implementations"],"generated":true}],"metadata":{"roleHeading":"Structure","modules":[{"name":"OpenSwiftUI"}],"remoteSource":{"url":"https:\/\/github.com\/OpenSwiftUIProject\/OpenSwiftUI\/blob\/main\/Sources\/OpenSwiftUICore\/Shape\/ShapeStyle\/Material.swift#L93","fileName":"Material.swift"},"symbolKind":"struct","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"Material","kind":"identifier"}],"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"Material"}],"externalID":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore8MaterialV","title":"Material","role":"symbol"},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A background material type."}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"Material"}],"platforms":["macOS"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"anchor":"overview","type":"heading","text":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You can apply a blur effect to a view that appears behind another view by"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"adding a material with the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"View\/background(_:ignoresSafeAreaEdges:)"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"modifier:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["ZStack {","    Color.teal","    Label(\"Flag\", systemImage: \"flag.fill\")","        .padding()","        .background(.regularMaterial)","}"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"In the example above, the ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/ZStack","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" layers a ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Label"},{"text":" on top of the color","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/ShapeStyle\/teal","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":". The background modifier inserts the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"regular material below the label, blurring the part of","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the background that the label — including its padding — covers:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A material isn’t a view, but adding a material is like inserting a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"translucent layer between the modified view and its background:"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The blurring effect provided by the material isn’t simple opacity. Instead,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"it uses a platform-specific blending that produces an effect that resembles"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"heavily frosted glass. You can see this more easily with a complex"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"background, like an image:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["ZStack {","    Image(\"chili_peppers\")","        .resizable()","        .aspectRatio(contentMode: .fit)","    Label(\"Flag\", systemImage: \"flag.fill\")","        .padding()","        .background(.regularMaterial)","}"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"For physical materials, the degree to which the background colors pass","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"through depends on the thickness. The effect also varies with light and","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"dark appearance:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"If you need a material to have a particular shape, you can use the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"View\/background(_:in:fillStyle:)","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" modifier. For example, you can","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"create a material with rounded corners:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["ZStack {","    Color.teal","    Label(\"Flag\", systemImage: \"flag.fill\")","        .padding()","        .background(.regularMaterial, in: RoundedRectangle(cornerRadius: 8))","}"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"When you add a material, foreground elements exhibit vibrancy,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"a context-specific blend of the foreground and background colors"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"that improves contrast. However using "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/View\/foregroundStyle(_:)","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to set a custom foreground style — excluding the hierarchical styles,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"like "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/ShapeStyle\/secondary-swift.type.property","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" — disables vibrancy."}]},{"style":"note","name":"Note","type":"aside","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A material blurs a background that’s part of your app, but not"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"what appears behind your app on the screen."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"For example, the content on the Home Screen doesn’t affect the appearance"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"of a widget."}]}]}]}],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/openswiftui\/material"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"kind":"symbol","identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Material","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"references":{"doc://OpenSwiftUI/documentation/OpenSwiftUI/ShapeStyle":{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A color or pattern to use when rendering a shape."}],"type":"topic","fragments":[{"text":"protocol","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"ShapeStyle","kind":"identifier"}],"role":"symbol","title":"ShapeStyle","kind":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"ShapeStyle","kind":"identifier"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/ShapeStyle","url":"\/documentation\/openswiftui\/shapestyle"},"doc://OpenSwiftUI/documentation/OpenSwiftUI/ShapeStyle/secondary-swift.type.property":{"role":"symbol","conformance":{"constraints":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Self"},{"text":" is ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"HierarchicalShapeStyle"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"conformancePrefix":[{"text":"Conforms when","type":"text"}],"availabilityPrefix":[{"text":"Available when","type":"text"}]},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A shape style that maps to the second level of the current content style."}],"kind":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"static"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"var"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"secondary"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore22HierarchicalShapeStyleV","text":"HierarchicalShapeStyle"}],"type":"topic","title":"secondary","url":"\/documentation\/openswiftui\/shapestyle\/secondary-swift.type.property","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/ShapeStyle\/secondary-swift.type.property"},"doc://OpenSwiftUI/documentation/OpenSwiftUI":{"kind":"symbol","role":"collection","url":"\/documentation\/openswiftui","type":"topic","title":"OpenSwiftUI","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Declare the user interface and behavior for your app on every platform."}]},"doc://OpenSwiftUI/documentation/OpenSwiftUI/Material/ShapeStyle-Implementations":{"title":"ShapeStyle Implementations","abstract":[],"kind":"article","type":"topic","role":"collectionGroup","url":"\/documentation\/openswiftui\/material\/shapestyle-implementations","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Material\/ShapeStyle-Implementations"},"doc://OpenSwiftUI/documentation/OpenSwiftUI/Material":{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A background material type."}],"type":"topic","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"Material"}],"title":"Material","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Material","role":"symbol","kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/openswiftui\/material","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"Material"}]},"doc://OpenSwiftUI/documentation/OpenSwiftUI/ZStack":{"fragments":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"ZStack","kind":"identifier"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A view that overlays its subviews, aligning them in both axes."}],"title":"ZStack","role":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/ZStack","url":"\/documentation\/openswiftui\/zstack","kind":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"ZStack","kind":"identifier"}],"type":"topic"},"doc://OpenSwiftUI/documentation/OpenSwiftUI/ShapeStyle/teal":{"kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/openswiftui\/shapestyle\/teal","type":"topic","title":"teal","abstract":[{"text":"A context-dependent teal color suitable for use i